cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR. 

The paper proposes a framework for modeling vision-and-language tasks, which involves natural language processing and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also extensively uses image data and proposes a novel approach for aligning text and image regions, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper proposes two visually-grounded language model objectives, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also conducts experiments and compares its results with state-of-the-art models, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval and natural language understanding, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
